By Oladele Eniola Badagry   –    A 20-year-old man, Abayomi Ogunbayo, who allegedly threatened to stab his friend, Bayo Adeite, with a knife, was on Monday brought before a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State. Ogunbayo, whose address was unknown, is facing a charge of threat to life. According to Prosecutor Akpan Ikem, the accused committed the offence on June 25, at Pota area of Badagry. Ikem said that the accused and his friend were arguing over how they would share a bottle of alcoholic drink. The prosecutor said that the accused brought out a knife and threatened to stab Adeite to death. “The two friends were embroiled in an argument over how they would share a bottle of alcoholic drink when the accused brought out a knife and threatened to stab his friend. “The complainant quickly ran out of the house to report the incident to the police,” he said. The prosecutor said that the offence contravened Section 56 (1), (A) of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2011. The accused, however, pleaded not guilty. Magistrate Jimoh Adefioye granted the accused bail in the sum of N100, 000 with a surety in like sum. Adefioye said that the surety must provide evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government as part of his bail conditions. The case was adjourned until Sept.12 for further hearing.